Seven persons, including an eight-month-old baby, died in an accident at Ugwuoba on the Enugu/Onitsha expressway. The accident involved an articulated vehicle (KTU 31 XA), as well as two Mitsubishi buses: XE 911 JJT and FGG 233 XG. A statement by spokesman Ebere Amaraizu said the articulated vehicle collided with one of the buses, which hit the other. The identities of the deceased were yet to be ascertained. Other injured passengers were rushed to Salvation and Faith Hospitals, Oji River. The bodies were deposited at General Hospital mortuary, Oji River. Amaraizu added that investigation has begun.